Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:32.14,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,原视频的小错误，这卫星是GOES系列的气象卫星，不是通信卫星(-_-#)\N该卫星介绍见av20451601
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.49,0:01:38.26,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,左边是定向天线 右边是全向天线
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:55.90,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,这个推力数值貌似是节流后的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.84,0:03:45.47,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,失败集锦av14923456
Dialogue: 1,0:00:01.44,0:00:08.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从早期的太空飞行开始火箭发射就一直很壮观
Dialogue: 2,0:00:01.44,0:00:08.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Ever since the early days of space-flight, rocket launches have been a fascinating spectacle
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.16,0:00:15.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即使到了现在，火箭升空仍然是发射中最一颗赛艇的环节
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.16,0:00:15.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Up until recently, lift-off has usually been the most tense and exciting part of any launch
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.04,0:00:20.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但当太空叉横空出世，开始搞火箭回收
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.04,0:00:20.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But ever since SpaceX came along and started to re-use their rockets
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.12,0:00:27.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,人们的目光开始更多地聚焦在猎鹰九号一级着陆上
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.12,0:00:27.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the landing of the Falcon 9 booster has become one of the most iconic shots in spaceflight
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.80,0:00:30.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当我们观看直播的时候就就就就就
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.80,0:00:30.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that is, when we get to see it
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.92,0:00:34.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可惜，我们发现太空叉的直播
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.92,0:00:34.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Sadly, when watching the SpaceX broadcast
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.88,0:00:41.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,经常会在火箭着陆前几秒卡顿，留给大家无尽悬念
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.88,0:00:41.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the live video feed often cuts out just as the rocket is coming into view, leaving us in suspense
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.49,0:00:43.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那这是为什么呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.49,0:00:43.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But why does this happen?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.16,0:00:51.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,本期视频，我们将了解太空叉如何获取着陆区的视频直播流
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.16,0:00:51.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In this video we are going to look at how SpaceX broadcasts live video from their landing sites
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.48,0:00:56.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并了解火箭是如何导致直播中断的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.48,0:00:56.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We’re also going to look at how the live feed is interrupted by the rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.92,0:01:02.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及应对此现象的可能的解决办法
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.92,0:01:02.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the possible solutions that could be put in place to get around this problem
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.01,0:01:08.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号一级火箭回到地球的时候，它要么落回陆地的着陆场
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.01,0:01:08.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the Falcon 9 lands back on Earth, it will either land back near the launch site
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.50,0:01:12.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,要么落在几百英里外大洋中的拖船上
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.50,0:01:12.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,or on a drone-ship placed hundreds of miles out in the ocean
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.00,0:01:21.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,想要从如此遥远位置的拖船传送直播数据，只能使用卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:14.00,0:01:21.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,With the drone-ship being in such a remote location the live video feed has to be transmitted via satellite
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.74,0:01:26.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,船上一个大天线直接把信号发给卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.74,0:01:26.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A large antenna on the drone-ship sends a directional signal towards the satellite
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.20,0:01:31.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,卫星之后把数据转发给地面的直播团队
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.20,0:01:31.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which will then transmit that footage back down to the broadcast team
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.49,0:01:38.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,船上天线必须是定向的，否则到达卫星的信号强度不够
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.49,0:01:38.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The signal from the drone-ship needs to be directional, in order for it to be strong enough to reach the satellite
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.39,0:01:42.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,于是当火箭接近拖船时就有问题了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.39,0:01:42.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The problem occurs when the rocket gets close to the drone-ship
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.50,0:01:49.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭准备着陆时，它会使用1台或3台梅林发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.50,0:01:49.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As it comes in for a landing, the rocket is slowed down using either 1 or 3 of it’s
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.06,0:01:55.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每台推力十万磅力（45吨），一起向拖船喷火
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.06,0:01:55.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Merlin engines each firing over 100,000lbs of thrust towards the surface of the drone-ship
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.32,0:02:02.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭离船越来越近时，火箭的推力会让船摇晃
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.32,0:02:02.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As the rocket gets closer to the drone-ship, the thrust from the engines start to shake the drone-ship
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.57,0:02:11.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,频率很高，会让天线失去对卫星的锁定，导致直播中断
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.57,0:02:11.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with such a high frequency that the video feed antenna loses lock with the satellite, causing the video feed to cut out
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.76,0:02:18.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当火箭着陆停稳，震动消失，直播就恢复了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.76,0:02:18.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Once the rocket has landed and the vibrations have dissipated, the video feed should reappear
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.72,0:02:22.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在这段时间，画面仍然会在拖船本地保存
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.72,0:02:22.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,During this period of time, the footage is recorded
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.54,0:02:26.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并在拖船恢复与卫星连接后马上补发
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.54,0:02:26.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and will be sent back as soon as the drone-ship regains connection with the satellite
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.22,0:02:31.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样做不但可以让工程师对每次着陆进行分析
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.22,0:02:31.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Not only does this ensure that the engineers can analyze each landing
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.71,0:02:38.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还能让太空叉在直播后上传完整录像供大家观看
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.71,0:02:38.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it also means that SpaceX can upload the footage after the broadcast for everyone else to watch
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.98,0:02:43.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,具体解决办法有很多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.98,0:02:43.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There have been many solutions put forward to fix this issue
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.20,0:02:48.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一种办法是在几百米外再放一个小船
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.20,0:02:48.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,One solution would be to have a similar ship placed a few hundred metres away from the
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.62,0:02:52.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,视频信号通过小船上天线与卫星连接
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.62,0:02:52.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,drone-ship with it’s own antenna to transmit the video feed
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.52,0:02:58.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样小船不会受到震动影响，缺点是它必须和拖船之间
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.52,0:02:58.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This antenna ship would be unaffected by the vibrations but it would need to be connected
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.73,0:03:04.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,使用非常长的视频线连接来传递数据
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.73,0:03:04.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to the drone-ship using a very long video cable to receive the footage
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.09,0:03:09.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然线缆可以用全向天线代替
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.09,0:03:09.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A way around this is to transmit the video feed from the drone-ship using a non directional
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.68,0:03:15.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,相当于使用小船再做一次直播数据的中继
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.68,0:03:15.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,signal to the antenna ship, which would then transmit the video feed up to the satellite
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.75,0:03:18.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从而避免受到火箭着陆时带来的震动
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.75,0:03:18.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,without being interrupted by the rockets vibrations
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.30,0:03:24.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管太空叉解决这种小问题SO EASY
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.30,0:03:24.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although this may seem like a problem that SpaceX could easily fix
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.97,0:03:28.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但这还要给整个回收过程增加一条船
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.97,0:03:28.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,going through the effort of adding more vessels to their recovery fleet
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.96,0:03:34.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,只为了流畅地看那么几秒的直播，有点不太值得
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.96,0:03:34.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,doesn’t seem like it’s worth the cost for just a few seconds of live video
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.84,0:03:39.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而且即使我们在着陆时看不到流畅的画面，那些画面也会被记录下来
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.84,0:03:39.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Even if we don’t get to see live footage of the landing, the footage is always recorded
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.60,0:03:42.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并且在几天后上传给大家看
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.60,0:03:42.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and uploaded a few days later for all of us to see
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.84,0:03:45.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即使着陆失败
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.84,0:03:45.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,even when the landing goes wrong
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.04,0:03:54.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因此尽管在回收最一颗赛艇的时候画面卡一下的确挺揪心
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.04,0:03:54.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So while it may be frustrating to lose the video feed right at the most exciting part of each mission
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.84,0:04:02.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但太空叉火箭回收的转播工作做的其实已经非常到位了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.84,0:04:02.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it does seem like SpaceX do everything they can to eventually bring us clear footage of each landing
